						<summary>

						<p>On the north wall of the central shrine, Ruined Vishṇu temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year: lost.</hi></p>						

						<p>It records a gift of 120 sheep for burning a perpetual lamp in the temple of Perumānaḍigaḷ at Gōvindapāḍi in Valla-nāḍu, (a division) of Dāmar-kōṭṭam, by Pañchavaṉ-Mahādēviyār, queen of Śōḻapperumāṉaḍigaḷ, who hailed from Kōṭṭūr in Nenmali-nāḍu, a division of Sōḻa-nāḍu.</p>						

						<p>The same queen figures in another inscription of this ruler in Sembiyanmahādēvi (See. No. 172).</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">S.I.I.,</hi> Vol. XIX. No. 445. </p>						

						</summary>
